pulltitle: fix https requests on windows, change loggedInEmail to loggedInUser
pullsbody:
Hello,

on windows you need to put the cabundle.crt near the script, to ensure that the https request can be made. (otherwise the raw-json result is just empty).

I changed the loggedInEmail (deprecated) in loggedInUser. Can't find any details of that, but its already forward compatible.

Best regards
Philipp
pull_repo_desc: UNMAINTAINED! Collection of simple browserid demos for different languages and platforms
pull_commit_message:
insert cabundle.crt for HTTPS requests on windows
change loggedInEmail(deprecated) in loggedInUser

pullsbody:
As discussed in #6 this updates the python examples to use [Requests](http://python-requests.org) instead of `urllib2` and enable SSL certificate checking.

I said I would like to do it for the django example, but since it seemed trivial to copy it to the other examples I took them along too. Besides, the web.py example is as much my responsibility as the django one is.
pull_repo_desc: UNMAINTAINED! Collection of simple browserid demos for different languages and platforms
pull_commit_message:
Make django example use python-requests

urllib2 doesn't check the validity of server SSL certificates.
